(40, 24, 44, 66, 19, 7, 7, 'be ye also ready', 'Readiness for the Coming', 'This connection highlights the theme of readiness in both passages. Matthew emphasizes being ready for the unexpected return of the Son of man, while Revelation speaks of the bride being ready for the marriage of the Lamb.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 44, 59, 5, 9, 9, NULL, 'Readiness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent arrival of judgment. Matthew 24:44 warns to be ready for the unexpected coming of the Son of Man, while James 5:9 reminds believers that the judge is near, urging them to avoid grievances.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
